{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@discardableResult"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"shadow"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"offset"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.davidbjames.C3\/documentation\/C3\/OffsetPair","preciseIdentifier":"s:2C310OffsetPairV","text":"OffsetPair"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"opacity"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CGFloat","preciseIdentifier":"s:12CoreGraphics7CGFloatV"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"radius"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CGFloat","preciseIdentifier":"s:12CoreGraphics7CGFloatV"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"color"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.davidbjames.C3\/documentation\/C3\/ColorDerivable","preciseIdentifier":"s:2C314ColorDerivableP","text":"ColorDerivable"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"masked"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"maskColor"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.davidbjames.C3\/documentation\/C3\/ColorDerivable","preciseIdentifier":"s:2C314ColorDerivableP","text":"ColorDerivable"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"with"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"transform"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.davidbjames.C3\/documentation\/C3\/Affine","preciseIdentifier":"s:2C36AffineV","text":"Affine"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"layerAlpha"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CGFloat","preciseIdentifier":"s:12CoreGraphics7CGFloatV"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.davidbjames.C3\/documentation\/C3\/Mutator","preciseIdentifier":"s:2C37MutatorV","text":"Mutator"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Mutator options (such as .random) affect “offset”."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Specify “masked” to support transparent or semi-transparent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"item(s) with the masked shadow being knocked out of the item(s)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Specify “maskColor” to be applied to the masked area of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shadow. If “masked” and “maskColor” are specified together"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the mask color can help make mask edge artifacts less visible and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in case of complex shapes – to fill in the parts of the shadow"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"mask that do not get knocked out properly – so that the masked"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"area blends with the background better. If “maskColor” is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified on it’s own then it will provide a color fill that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"occupies the shape of the item(s)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"NOTE: If item(s) already have layer addons, or transform\/alpha"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are applied, or “masked” == true, or “maskColor” is specified,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then the shadow will be represented as a Layer Addon which"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can then be animated independent of the item(s)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"NOTE: For applying shadows to text see also TextShape object which"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can better represent shadows (as a shape) than TextLayers can."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(Masking on most typographical items causes the shadow mask"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to be applied to the layer and not to the text.)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"NOTE: When applying a shadow to a composed shape (a shape made"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of multiple overlapping subpaths) the overlapping parts of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"composed shape will show the mask color rather than being"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"knocked out as expected. This is because the knockout uses"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an even-odd fill rule which inverts overlapping areas (that is,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"“unmasking” parts that should be masked). To resolve this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(assuming it’s a visible issue) create the path externally"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(e.g. via PaintCode) such that it is a properly unioned shape"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(not a compound shape) and add that via AnyShape()."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":2,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/c3\/mutator\/shadow(offset:opacity:radius:color:masked:maskcolor:with:layeralpha:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.davidbjames.C3\/documentation\/C3\/Mutator\/shadow(offset:opacity:radius:color:masked:maskColor:with:layerAlpha:)","interfaceLanguage":"s